caption: Got breakfast from here through DoorDash and was really impressed with how everything came and how everything tasted!!! 5/5, definitely would order again! :)

Very cute spot. Cozy but not too small. Right downtown tucked in across from the mass mutual center. The cook does it all. He took out order and got us our coffee. The food was hot, fresh and delicious. We each had omelets, home-fries and coffee. There was metered parking one block over.
Today I ordered the steak and cheese stuffed avocado.  Not only was it a beautiful presentation, it was delicious!!
AH-MAY-ZING!!!  The food was fresh, the staff was super friendly, and the atmosphere was quaintly adorable.  Honestly, so wonderfully delicious!  I can't say enough good things!
Garlic Chicken is so good, the Mofongo, the stuffed avocado AMAZING. The Salads always FRESH! Call ahead to get your orders.

What a great dining experience! Visited on the recommendation of a friend and was not disappointed. Excellent soul/comfort food. Cozy atmosphere and family friendly. The owners are super nice, community conscious and their young kids are cooking and handling the business. I had the smothered pork chops and don't know if I'll try anything else because they were sooooo good.

This is an upscale hidden gem at VERY affordable prices specially aiming at those that are not willing to sacrifice quality but have a strict lunch budget. IT IS A MUST SEE!!!

We live locally and I'm honestly surprised that people gave this restaurant some of the reviews that I read below. This restaurant is a gem and classic in western mass. It has always been a great restaurant with amazing food and really incredible staff.I would highly recommend going there to experience the atmosphere as well as some great food!

My buddy an I both had the fish sandwich. He hand battered it an fried it right there on the spot. It was a dinner sized portion of fish on a bun. It was delicious fries were great and it was quick. We walked in here on a whim not knowing where to eat in the area for lunch. Now we know 👍👍

The place has a small home town vibe. Unfortunately I was not greeted nor was acknowledged once I took a sit at the counter it took a few more minutes of recognition. Finally recognized I ordered the omelette with Spinach and tomato plus a side of pancakes. Pancakes were decent but the omelette was bad, still wet on the inside. The water I also ordered, well I had to ask again for it.  I also had to ask for the check as the worker were busy on their phones.  I really tried to like this place but every turn was unsuccessful.

Clean place to eat, friendly cashier/cook. I had ordered Togo and when I received my order I noticed the bag was a little light. PORTIONS, PORTIONS, PORTIONS. What is going on the small burger was ok as far as taste then the fries just the same. I'm surprised, I'm not at all greedy nor do I expect a 5 lb plate but you can do better. I'm a chef myself I understand. If your going to serve child size meals ADJUST,and compliment it with a child size price. P.S. So I've noticed a heaping amount of Ketchup. Thank you ,removed it from the bag and it became a alot lighter. I see why the place hidden ??

Probably better off going to Tower Grill at Tower Square where the cost for a burger and fries is the same but you receive a better portion and food.
